<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="674" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d674">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 365.117/282.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State ad
                                    interim</gloss> to Ambassador <persName type="to">Page</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-10">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 10, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>256. Your 318, 8th. Enrico Ajello was born in New York City, March 15,
                            1882. Father naturalized October 25, 1889. With exception short business
                            trip Italy 1906, has resided continuously this country. Ask release,
                            referring Department’s telegram 7th concerning Ghiloni. Report. Ajello
                            case previously taken up with Consul Naples.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>